Pre-Game Insights: The Netherlands are within a point of guaranteeing progress to the knockout stages after their final Group F fixture against Austria.
Brian Brobbey has recovered from a hamstring injury and is competing with Wout Weghorst for a starting spot up front.
Ronald Koeman may opt for continuity in the final third, with Memphis Depay likely spearheading the 4-2-3-1 formation.
Cody Gakpo, Xavi Simons, and either Yeremie Frimpong or Donyell Malen are expected to provide support from behind.
Tijjani Reijnders is set to keep his place in midfield, with possible changes in defense to freshen up the solid back four.
Bart Verbruggen has established himself as the Netherlands' number one goalkeeper, starting nine of their last 10 matches.
